('Sph12-38', 'MIC 3 micro M against Staphylococcus aureus, Corynebacterium glutamicum, Micrococcus lysodeikticus Fleming, Bacillus subtilis, Pseudomonas fluorescens, Aeromonas hydrophila and A. sobria', '', 'Taken together, the synthetic peptide of Sph12-38 had a potent antimicrobial activity against bacteria.', 28600196),
('Free or anchored antimicrobial peptides like  the cathelicidins BMAP-27 and BMAP-28, their (1-18) fragments and the rationally designed, artificial P19(9/G7) peptide', 'Effective at micromolar concentrations against 22 Staphylococcus and Streptococcus isolates from orthopaedic infections,  BMAP-28 and to a lesser extent BMAP-27 were active against Enterococcus faecalis', 'Negligible toxicity towards osteoblasts', 'Alpha-helical antimicrobial peptides (AMPs) may be promising candidates in this respect due to their potent and broad-spectrum antimicrobial activity, their low tendency to elicit resistance and possible retention of efficacy in the immobilized state.', 28707817),
